headline: Ex-NCAA Prez Emmert Unloads Shares of Logistics Firm Expeditors
summary: Mark Emmert, the former NCAA president, recently sold 4,100 shares of Expeditors International, a Bellevue, Wash.-based company where he has served on the board of directors since 2008. When he was appointed to the board, Emmert was president of the University of Washington, three years before he took over leadership of the NCAA. According to …
